The paper discusses Adversarial Optimization (AO) and proposes a novel family of divergences that can accelerate the optimization process for computationally heavy generators. This work is primarily focused on machine learning and optimization techniques, which suggests that it is likely to belong to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-category. Additionally, the paper mentions several tasks related to computer vision (cs.CV), physics simulation (cs.SY), and neural networks (cs.NE), which further supports the likelihood of these sub-categories. Finally, the use of high-capacity models and optimization techniques also suggests that the paper may belong to the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-category.
